item.title: What is fixture congestion and what can teams do to combat it?
item.description: This week, we're taking a look at the scourge of the modern game: fixture congestion. Is it indeed a problem exclusive to the modern era? What can teams do to ease the workload? What can happen when a player is ‘red lining’? And the most important question: are we reaching breaking point? WE HAVE A YOUTUBE CHANNEL! We're posting all our episodes here! Smash the like and subscribe etc... Feed: https://feeds.megaphone.fm/TAMC3158268863

item.title: 148 Tornadoes in 18 Hours
item.description: April 3, 1974. Across America, many people wake up this morning thinking it will be a normal day. But in the next 24 hours, almost 150 tornadoes will hit the United States. It will be the largest tornado outbreak in the nation's history... Feed: https://feeds.megaphone.fm/history-this-week
